ottnball.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cottnball</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_greenspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/30/01 6:46:08 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Weapon Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> I am a 44 Barbarian Warrior who has not upgraded weapons in quite a while.  I have some cash saved up (3k) and was hoping you could give me some suggestions for upgrading my weapons.  In my normal group I am usually assisting the main tank.<br>
<br>
Assist Setup<br>
Primary: Wurmslayer (aka 'The Devil')<br>
Secondary: Cane of the Tranquil<br>
<br>
High Taunt<br>
Primary: Cane of the Tranquil<br>
Secondary: Crystallized Sword<br>
<br>
1HS (200) - Wurmslayer (40/25), Crysallized Sword (29/11)<br>
1HB (200) - Cane of the Tranquil (25/11)<br>
2HS (150) - Blade of Xalgoz (40/23)<br>
2HB (50) - Mithril Staff (45/28) <br>
1HP (150) - Harpoon of the Depths (25/8) , Walrus Tooth (22/6)<br>
<br>
A friend has offered to sell me a Kunzar Ku'juch for 1,700pp.  Is this a good upgrade?  I'd like to get something to replace my wurmslayer with but its hard to beat the damage it deals out without getting something out of my price range.<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
Potch Tape<br>
Sleeping Giant<br>
Innoruuk Server <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucottnball.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cottnball</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_greenspot.gif BORDER=0> at: 6/4/01 11:38:13 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/01 9:57:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Weapon Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> Get in a KC captains group and pray for a jade mace. I am not all the familiar with the higher mid level weapons, but you look to be at the point where it is going to cost you to udgrade. To make it worth your while, you should probably be looking at jade maces and lammys. If you don't have a haste item, you might consider a Mith 2 hander until you can afford a Truncheon or Felhammer. I could be wrong though. Any thoughts guys?? <p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 45th Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i><p>
<span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Moordian Killbringer<br>Warrior of 22 Battle Scars</b><br><i>Dwarven LaMachine of Death</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utalicmoore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talic Moore</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 240<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/01 10:41:34 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/classes/c_warrior.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Weapon Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> For piercing a recommend a Jarsath Trident (11/22) Great off-hand weapon.<br>
<br>
Ditch the Wurmslayer as SOON as you can. Lamentations are good once you can do Seb. It and the Jade Mace are now pretty much the bread and butter of a higher level warrior.<br>
<br>
For 2hs Felhammer is good, though I personally prefer Zealots Incarnadine Sword (Also drops in Sebilis)<br>
<br>
For 2hb, Truncheon, Stormwood, etc.<br>
<br>
Again, lose the Wurmslayer as soon as you get something else. It's the devil. <p><b><u>Talic Asaria Moore</b></u> <BR>
<i>Champion of the Realm of Heroes</i> <BR>
<a href=mailto:talicmoore@hotmail.com>talicmoore@hotmail.com</a><BR>


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uddarkreaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ddarkreaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/01 10:54:50 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://208.162.125.24/eq/family/images/heads/darias_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Weapon Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> If you can hold out on upgrades for a bit, and save another 2-3k (giving you around 6k), then  you could sell your WS for 3k and pick up a lammy/mace for around 9k (using CT prices).  Then you can use that in main and cane in off-hand until you can upgrade your off-hand.<br>
<br>
As a 44 warrior, you will probably not get into a Karnors group (at least not LC), and definitely not Seb, so buying is your only option at this point.<br>
<br>
Darias Darkreaver<br>
53 Barbarian Champion<br>
Cazic Thule <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uddarkreaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ddarkreaver</A> at: 5/31/01 10:59:04 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udoslo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Doslo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/01 4:30:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Weapon Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> I have the same sorta question, except I have all my weapons.  Right now I'm carrying so many weapons, I feel like an armory. =P<br>
<br>
Right now my primary hand uses either a lammy or a faydark bladecatcher (it's that 10/21 10ac sword that procs an aoe).<br>
<br>
For my secondary hand, I use one of these: snare whip, css, or jarsath trident.<br>
<br>
I still can't figure out the best combination that I can rely on 90% of the time or at least what I can leave in the bank.  Any suggestions?<br>
<br>
Dos <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucottnball.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cottnball</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_greenspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/4/01 11:39:11 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> Thanks for your help.<br>
<br>
I'll try and sell off some stuff I have in the bank and look for a lamentation or jade mace.  It seems that is the next logical step for me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uchamp2040.showPublicProfile?language=EN>champ2040</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/4/01 12:06:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  kunzar ku'juch</span><hr size=1> The kunzar ku'juch i believe is 8/22, but it procs engulfing darkness.  I have no idea how good that proc is, but that is a great price if you need the weapon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushikariiapoccalypse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shikarii Apoccalypse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 222<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/4/01 12:56:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: kunzar ku'juch</span><hr size=1> i gave up my kunzar when i got my 1st lamentation ( at level 53 ). loved the thing.<br>
<br>
the engulfing darkness is nice when you're in small groups and don't have a snare/root/slow person with you. and in the primary hand it proc'd quite a bit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gangleri>Gangleri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/5/01 12:51:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Weapon Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> Since you already have 3k+ id suggest just keep saving your dough and do whatever you have to and get more to buy an Haste item. <br>
 That will, in my opinion be the wisest investment. Maybe even sell or offer the wurm in partial trade for a fbss or whatever if you have to. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushaeol.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shaeol</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/5/01 12:20:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Weapon Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> Aye a kujuch is a nice weapon.  I use it until I can upgrade to jade mace/lammy.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Shaeol<br>
47 Warrior <br>
Dragon Maw <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/unailened.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nailened</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/6/01 8:23:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Weapon Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> Okay.  Here's my suggestion.  Save your cash or use it to buy some armor upgrades and work on AC.  Keep your weapons and get some levels behind you to get to 47 or 48.  Then get your barb ass to Karnor's Castle.  Get in a Tower group.  I've gotten 2 Jade Maces in 6 levels of good exp in KC.  Yes it gets boring.  However, in addition, you can also get a chance at cobalt guantlets off Drolvarg Captain and then later cobalt boots off Caller of Sathir in a courtyard group.  LOTS of decent drops in KC and decent exp to 54 when you can head to Seb.  I traded my maces for a lammy and cash and a css and some cash.  The maces themselves are very nice weapons.  When you can hit seb you can hope for cobalt vambs, css , lammy and truncheon / stormwood for your 2hb upgrade!  GOOD LUCK brother warrior! (even though you are a barbarian)<br>
<br>
Lomax Loatheheart<br>
54th Dwarven Champion<br>
Hope's Beginning<br>
Vazaelle<br>
